[It is fortunate that no instances of ongoing transmission in the DRC from the cases imported from Angola have been detected. One hopes that there is adequate surveillance in the localities in the DRC where the positive YF cases have been reported, to detect any transmission and new cases should they occur. If local transmission is occurring, swift response is needed to intensify surveillance with laboratory support and mount a vaccination campaign in the affected area.

Control at the DRC-Angola border s prudent. Because the Angola-DRC border is likely to be leaky, it is probable that additional infected individuals may cross into the DRC. The coordination of health officials on both sides of the border will be helpful in restricting the flow of infected individuals across the border. - Mod.TY

Kongo Central province is also known as Bas Congo (formerly Bas Zaire) and can be found on a map at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/dr_congo_map.htm. It borders Angola on its south and west, the Republic of Congo on its north, Kinshasa to its northeast, and Bandundu to its east. - Mod.MPP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of the country can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4122415,40817.

Re Yellow fever - Africa (30): Mauritania ex Angola 20160326.4119691: the fatal case was also imported. Mauritania is a dengue-endemic country and therefore at high risk of ongoing transmission. - Mod.JW]
